text: Today I am in DC, but I am sending my love to my first valentine, my mother, and I will spend the evening telling my wife Monica and my girls Sky and Sage the many ways I love and appreciate them. Happy Valentine’s Day!
Unacceptable. I will not stop working for you during this government shutdown. My office will be open to answer your questions and concerns. I am here to serve you.

I have been working tirelessly for long-term, bipartisan, budget solutions that will help our government serve the American people. Unfortunately, Congress voted on yet another stop gap, temporary funding measure today. 1/4
Dreamers are hardworking students and young people in our military who make incredible contributions to our economy and help keep our nation secure. 1/4

On #LawEnforcementAppreciationDay we honor the incredible public safety officers who rush into harm’s way each day to keep us safe. RT to join me in thanking them and their families for their service!

I am so grateful to spend today with my family, counting our blessing as this year comes to a close and making our goals for the year to come. I hope everyone has a moment to reflect on 2017 and I wish you a joyous new year!
Monica, Sky, Sage, and I wish you and your family a very Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays! Wishing everyone health and happiness in 2018!
This joyous season, let us show gratitude to the brave men and women in uniform who are often away from their families serving our nation and keeping us safe. Thank you for your service!
Today the House passed my bipartisan Wildfire Prevention Act, a huge win for our district!

Today I voted against the tax plan that forces $100B in cuts to Medicare over the next 4 years and increase taxes on tens of millions of middle-class families. It gives 83% of the tax breaks to the wealthiest 1% and explodes the deficit by $1.5 trillion.

My thoughts and prayers are with those injured in today's attack in NYC. Thank you to all the brave law enforcement officers and first responders who rushed into danger and helped save lives. We stand united with the people of New York.
Today the House passed a long-overdue bill to require anti-harassment and anti-discrimination training for members and staff. I require this of my staff and every Member should do the same.
Wishing you a Happy Thanksgiving from me, my wife Monica, and my girls Sky and Sage!

We all rely on the internet — to apply for jobs, further our education, stay in touch with our family and friends, and even read this tweet. Unfortunately, today's proposal by the FCC to roll back existing #netneutrality oversight will eliminate critical consumer protections…
I am grateful for the courage survivors of sexual harassment and abuse have shown in telling their stories and am furious at the unacceptable behavior they have experienced. 1/3
Millions of middle-class families will see a tax increase under the current tax proposal. Retweet if you oppose raising taxes on millions of hardworking Americans.
I do want to simplify our tax code and I do want tax reform, a tax reform that relieves the burden on the middle class, seniors, veterans, and students. 1/3
Breaking News – My bipartisan bill to amend the ACA and protect Medicare from arbitrary cuts passed the House!
Rural, underserved communities are more vulnerable to environmental and health threats...
Last week, Trump admin continued the harmful sabotage of the ACA by ending cost-sharing subsidies. Fight to #ProtectOurCare continues!
On National #ComingOutDay be an ally to people living openly as their authentic selves and celebrate the pride of #LGBTQHistoryMonth!
The 3.6 million U.S. citizens in #PuertoRico & #USVI deserve our focused attention. RT to show your support for our #OurFellowAmericans.
Gave my family an extra hug today and praying for anyone who lost a loved one or was injured by the horrific events in Las Vegas last night.
Puerto Rico suffered a major disaster that will only get worse without immediate and robust relief efforts. 1/8
It's a critical week in the fight to #ProtectOurCare, so here are the most harmful parts of #GrahamCassidy, worst version of #Trumpcare 1/16
The #GrahamCassidy bill would mean far worse care for patients, far fewer Americans covered, and much higher costs for hardworking families.
Fight to #ProtectOurCare isn't over. Trump administration is still undermining #ACA by not committing to funding cost-sharing subsidies.
We remember the lives lost, families impacted, & bravery of law enforcement & first responders & stand united against hate #NeverForget
Just voted to pass a bill that provides $7.9B in relief funding for #HurricaneHarvey to help families and communities rebuild.
Ending #DACA goes against the very core of our values as Americans. (1/4)
Today we celebrate #SocSec82!Over 60M Americans rely on Social Security and we must continue to protect and expand it for our seniors.
#Trumpcare has failed and we must  work together and pass my Marketplace Certainty Act NOW to address rising costs and market instability.
Key vote on Senate #Trumpcare today. All versions of the bill still hurt patients. Keep fighting to #ProtectOurCare
Intro’d Marketplace Certainty Act to fund Cost Sharing Reductions & increase eligibility. Will stabilize markets & help patients afford care
Senate GOP releasing updated #Trumpcare today. Fundamentals will still hurt patients and raise costs for seniors and working families.
About to join @CNNnewsroom to discuss impact of #Trumpcare on patients. Tune in at around 9:35ET/6:35PT.
#CBOScore confirms 15M more uninsured in 1 year & 22M more in 10 years. This bill isn't just mean; it's cruel, deadly, and must be stopped.
#Comey hearing underscores importance of a truly independent investigation. Not about party or politics, but the future of our democracy.
Leaving the climate accord is bad for our environment, health, and future.
#CBO score shows AHCA is still devastating with 23M more uninsured over a decade. This is far too great a toll on the American people.
POTUS budget cuts programs that invest in our health & economic security. We should invest in everyone not just millionaires & corporations.
Thanks to everyone who came to Veterans University! It was an honor hearing your stories and I look forward to continuing our work together.
On National Peace Officers Memorial Day, we remember those who gave ultimate sacrifice and thank those who serve and their families.
What does #TrumpCare mean for older Americans? The bill would impose an age tax on people over 50.
#TrumpCare 2.0 makes 129 million with pre-existing illnesses subject to high costs and coverage discrimination. Unacceptable!
GOP wants to force vote on revised #TrumpCare without analysis of grave consequences it would have on patients. Absolutely unacceptable!
On #HolocaustRemembranceDay, we honor the lives of those lost at the hands of the Nazis and recommit ourselves to fighting against hatred.
What is POTUS hiding? My Ethics Package will shed light on conflicts of interest. #TaxDay #peopleoverpolitics
Breaking News: Enough Republicans agree #TrumpCare is bad for patients across the country and cancel the health care bill vote for now.
Late night deals make the AHCA worse for the American people. My fight #ProtectOurCare & lower health care costs continues!
Unacceptable that #TrumpCare is going to raise health care costs for Americans, especially those in rural communities. #PayMoreForLess
#TrumpCare is opposed by hospitals, doctors & patients advocates because it would force Americans to #PayMoreForLess
.@maddow is right. Need my Ethics Package to shed light on conflicts of interests that put national security at risk #peopleoverpolitics
Per CBO score, 24 million uninsured by 2026 under GOP health care bill, all while cutting taxes for the rich. We must #ProtectOurCare!
Markup may be over but my fight for high-quality, affordable health care for everyone continues. We must #ProtectOurCare @EnergyCommerce
About to go live on @MSNBC with @SRuhle to talk about fight to #ProtectOurCare. Tune in at 9:18.
We must have the chance to review GOP #ACA bill before next week’s markup but GOP is keeping it secret. RT to ask the GOP #WheresTheBill
David from @DesertAIDS and I are heading to the House chamber for tonight’s address. Stay tuned for updates on #JointSession
Excited to announce David Brinkman of @DesertAIDS is my #JointSession guest! DAP does incredible work to bring health care to #CA36
Enjoyed talking with @andreag_tv today about the future of #ACA and my Ethics Package #peopleoverprofit. Gracias @NU34LA
We must keep up the fight to protect our health and environment for generations to come #LCVScorecard
We must protect public lands & wildlife, ensure clean air & water, & fund critical research that improves environmental health #LCVScorecard
As an emergency physician and public health expert, I know that environmental health is undeniably linked to human health #LCVScorecard
Joining @LCVoters to unveil their 2016 Environment Scorecard today. Follow along at #LCVScorecard for more!
You may have seen I've been tweeting about my Ethics Package. I want to give you a few reasons why this is necessary #peopleoverprofit
Joining @bpshow to talk about my ethics package and how public service is about #peoplenotprofit. Tune in at 8:30ET.
We need a health care system that has strong protections for Americans with pre-existing conditions #ProtectOurCare
Troubled by report the USACE will grant easement for #DAPL. Disregards tribal sovereignty and health risks of a spill for @StandingRockST.
Time to #StopSessions, he has not proven that he will work to uphold justice for everyone no matter their background.
Regardless of background, race, ethnicity or religion, everyone deserves fairness & equality under the law. That's why we must #StopSessions
Today is National Law Enforcement Appreciation Day. Thank you to our brave men & women who protect our communities! #ThankACop
Happy New Year! Spending time reflecting on 2016 tonight with my family.
Happy Holidays from me, my wife Monica, and my girls Sky and Sage!
Today is #LaborDay. A day to recognize the workers who keep our country running. Thank you for your hard work!

Evacuation has been lifted for Banning Bench area due to #BogartFire. Residents can return to their homes with valid I.D. Please stay
alert.
300+ firefighters fighting a rapid growing fire in Cherry Valley. Highland Springs Village Mobile Home Park is being evacuated.  #BogartFire
Anniversary of the #19thAmendment which gave women the right to vote. Crucial moment in the fight for #EqualityforWomen
Happy Birthday #NationalParkService! Let’s keep supporting their work to keep National Parks alive for future generations.
51st anniversary of Medicare & Medicaid. Proud to fight to protect these programs that provide crucial services to countless individuals.
26th anniversary of the Americans with Disabilities Act becoming law. Crucial to protecting rights for the disabled. @USDOL
Saddened to hear of passing of @RepMarkTakai. He was always incredibly friendly and a strong advocate for Native Hawaiians #MahaloMark
#PrayForBatonRouge. My prayers go out for the officers killed & wounded in Baton Rouge & my condolences goes out to their families.
51 yrs since #OlderAmericansAct became law. Provides crucial services for seniors like home delivered meals. Proud to continue the fight.
Doctors, nurses, first responders - join me to demand a vote to protect our patients from gun violence #holdthefloor
Thinking of gun violence victims I cared for in ER, did everything to keep them alive. Some lived & some died, all suffered #holdthefloor
I'm sitting on the House floor demanding a vote to lift the ban on gun violence research  #holdthefloor
Sad & disturbing news from my alma mater @UCLA today. Thank you to law enforcement for keeping students and faculty safe.
In US, +1500 have #Zika, 78 die each day due to opioids & 1000's face damage b/c #FlintWaterCrisis. @HouseGOP: #DoYourJob & act meaningfully
On #NationalPoliceWeek let’s recognize our men & women in Law Enforcement that keep us safe. Thank you for your service.
#House voted on 17 bills this week to address #opioidaddiction. This is progress but our work isn’t finished.
Thank you @MilkenInstitute @CristinaAlesci @CNN @VulcanInc @daraerck @TakedaPharma for discussing important issues. #Ebola #Zika #pandemics

text: Disappointed that Speaker Ryan allowed House to adjourn without emergency funding for the Zika Virus. Advocacy will continue. @CDCgov
I joined my colleagues from both sides of the aisle to urge a hearing on the #EqualityAct. Let’s bring it to a vote ASAP. @DesertAIDS  @HRC
Today is #EarthDay. Let’s fix the #SaltonSea to provide #renewableenergy & attract #tourism. @IIDatWork @USFWS @NatlParkService
Met with Pres. of @WorldBank Dr. Jim Kim & Geoffrey Cowan from @SunnylandsNews to discuss internatl. response to pandemics like #ZikaVirus
Congrats to those recognized at #PoliceandFireAppreciationLuncheon. We honor your service and TY for keeping us safe. @CALFIRERRU #PSPolice
VA actions don’t align with goals and mission. Contact my office if you have any issues scheduling an appointment with the VA: 760-424-8888
TY to all 911 dispatchers in my Dist. & the nation for your dedication to server our communities. #NPSTW2016 #CA36
Women in general make 79₵ & Latinas make 55₵ for every dollar earned by men. Close the #PayGap & pass the #PaycheckFairnessAct #EqualPayDay
#NationalMinorityHealthAwarenessMonth. I will continue to fight for #HealthEqulity in our communities. @Minority Health
Honored to support H.R. 4336, the WASP AIR Act that will allow Women who flew in WWII to be inurned at @ArlingtonNationalCemetery.
Happy National Doctors Day. @EisenhowerMed, @JFKMemorialHosp, @DesertRegionalMedicalCenter, #PaloVerdeHospital, #HemetValleyMedicalCenter
On March 23rd, 1868 @UofCalifornia system was founded. Let's make education more affordable. @UCLA @UCRiverside @UCRSoM @UCRPalmDesert
Congrats to #CesarChavezElementarySchool for their 25th anniv. & for honoring Cesar Chavez, an American  hero @C_V_U_S_D
We mourn for the victims of #brusselsattack & show our support for the survivors & families
Daylight Saving Time on Sunday. Don’t forget, Spring your clock one hour on Saturday night! #DaylightSaving #SpringForward
TY to the all Read With Me Volunteer who donate their time to read to students in communities of the #CA36District
Let’s celebrate progress on #IWD2016. We still have a lot of work to do for #GenderEquality. #PledgeForParity
Sent a letter to @SpeakerRyanc urging him to provide funding to fight #Zika virus. We must heed @CDC @NIH warnings to stop the disease.
TY to all local law enforcement who participated in gang sweep under Operation Safe Coachella 16.1 & for keeping us safe @RSO
Today @ #CoachellaValleyScore legislative breakfast I highlighted my legislative jobs package & local small businesses advocacy successes.
TY to all vets for attending the biannual Veterans listening forum @cityofBeaumont & TY to @valomalinda & @VASanDiego for participating.
This week I advocated for vets whose credit was hurt by delayed medical bill payments by 3rd parties. Need help? Call my office 760-424-8888
Another victory in getting $3million in @interior funds to rehabilitate @Visitsaltonsea & prevent future toxic dust particles at #SaltonSea.
Today is National Wear Red Day. Let’s #GoRedForWomen to fight against heart disease in women.
Let’s celebrate #BlackHistory by remembering the contributions of African Americans to our great country and #CA36district
76 years ago today, the 1st Social Security check was issued. I'll continue to stand with seniors and strengthen #SocialSecurity. #CA36
43 years after #SCOTUS decision on Roe v. Wade, we still see violence & harassment. I support H.Res. 558 condemning these acts.
Today I voted to protect women’s access to @PPFA clinics that provide preventative and life-saving health care.
Heartbroken to learn of George Zander's passing. He was a great leader and friend. My thoughts & prayers are with the Zander Family @eqca
Today I voted for the America SAFE Act, allowing refugees a safe haven in the US while keeping our nation secure. #USHouse #Syrianrefugees
In Dec. 2012, I presented my vision to Sen. Boxer and then Secy. Salazar. We got to work on #RedHillBayProject.  #4SaltonSeaRestoration
I condemn the attack against George & Chris Zander. Hate crimes against an @LGBT group is a hate crime against our community @EQCA
Thanks to the participants of this VA Health emerging tech round table. The goal is to take care of all generations of Vets. #TheyveEarnedIt
During LGBT History Month, let’s recognize the brave individuals and groups who have helped to empower the LGBT community. @DesertAIDS @eqca
Early earthquake detection is a #nobrainer. May save lives/property. I urge .@POTUS to support more funding for .@usgs technologies! #Ruiz36
TY to all participants of the 2015 @patriot_ride1 & those in uniform who participated. #RuizCA36,
#CA36 constituents to see #Popeindc. TY to all who participated in lottery! @Pontifex
We need a robust, long-term bill that builds the safe, modern infrastructure that our country deserves & our economy needs. #RebuildRenew
Congratulations to the U.S. women's team on their World Cup victory! #USWNT #USAvJPN
I am deeply saddened to hear of the tragic shooting in #Charleston. My family & I are keeping all those affected in our thoughts & prayers.
This #EqualPayDay, I urge my colleagues to join me in support of the Paycheck Fairness Act to ensure women earn equal pay for equal work.
The “religious freedom” law passed in IN allows for sanctioned discrimination against the LGBT community & has no place in our society.
Today we honor holocaust survivors, those lost, and recommit ourselves to ending genocide around the globe #HolocaustRememberanceDay
Sitting w/ my friend & @HouseVetAffairs colleague @RepWalorski for the #SOTU. Looking fwd to continuing to work together for our #veterans.
Saturday@ #eqcaawards was an incredible gathering of public servants & activists! Thank you for all you do to make our nation a better place
Thank you to everyone who made today's Desert AIDS Walk a success. #desertaidswalk
Proud to have advocated for & received $7 million in @USDA grants to bring clean water services to underserved communities in the #CV
With @MCS4Biz at the @CVEPartnership to discuss ways to spur business development in the #CoachellaValley with local entrepreneurs
"Rep. Ruiz has helped to secure grants for CVEP... we thank you for your advocacy & leadership" Tom Flavin of @CVEPartnership
This #LaborDay let us honor the hard work of countless American families whose commitment helped to forge the greatest nation in the world.
Tomorrow, I'll in the #CV with @SBAgov meeting w/ #SmallBusinesses to talk innovation, entrepreneurship, and #job creation in our community.
Honored to host @SBAgov & small business owners in the #CV to discuss #job creation, resources SBA offers small business.
I am honored to bring the US Small Business Admin to the #CoachellaValley to discuss innovation, entrepreneurship, & creating #jobs @SBAgov

On the anniversary of the 19th Amendment, we celebrate #WomensEqualityDay.
Our work isn't done - equality means #paycheckfairness.
For 79 years @SocialSecurity has safeguarded our right to #retire with dignity. Today we renew our commitment to this vital program.
This week, w/ a group of bipartisan lawmakers, I introduced the #SaveAct to reign in $102 bill in wasteful gov spending over the next 10 yrs
Congrats to Team USA on their win against Ghana! #WorldCup2014
It‘s with a heavy heart that I learned of the passing of Nelson Mandela. His memory will continue to be a source of strength & inspiration.
Let's take a step in the fight to end discrimination.196 House Ds & Rs signed on to #passENDA. The Senate voted & it's time the House act.
My thoughts & prayers are w/all affected by the tragedy at Navy Yard in DC – esp victims, their families, & first responders on scene.
Today, as we honor the fallen, let us reaffirm our commitment to each other & recall what we are capable of when standing together.
I'll be on the ground tomorrow meeting w/ officials at the Garner Valley Command Center and surveying the damage caused by the #MountainFire
Excited for today's @NoLabelsOrg #ProblemSolvers event -- we're talking about how to #MakeGovernmentWork in a #bipartisan way. Stay tuned!
Tomorrow I'll be standing with 60+ of my bipartisan #NoLabels #ProblemSolvers colleagues in DC to unveil our #MakeGovernmentWork initiative
The Mountain Fire is headed toward Palm Springs. It's very aggressive and spreading quickly. For more info, call Cal Fire at (909) 383-5688
Tomorrow my office is hosting a free federal grants workshop focusing on arts&humanities from 1:30-3:30 PM at UCR-Palm Desert, Room B200
Happy to see the FOR #VETS Act pass the House tonight with strong bipartisan support. I cosponsored this bill to help VSOs
Wishing you and your family a happy and safe 4th of July!  Thank you to our servicemen and women for protecting our freedom #IndependenceDay
On the anniversary of the Civil Rights Act, let's celebrate the progress we've made and pledge ourselves to the work that remains #equality
Very saddened by the news that 19 heroes lost their lives battling the wildfire in AZ. Thoughts & prayers are w/ their families and friends
The passage of the bipartisan Senate #CIR bill today is a step in the right direction. It's time now for the House to take action!
.@vpelham's @mydesert story on CA children's health is deeply troubling. We must improve education, access to high-quality care for our kids
Pleased that the Senate took #bipartisan action last night to bring us closer to #CIR. Time now for the House to follow their lead and act!
It's the 50th annual National #smallbiz Week! Thanks to all the 36th District small businesses for your enormous contribution to our economy
Wishing the @USArmy a very happy 238th birthday! Our soldiers have always fought valiantly to defend the freedoms we all hold dear
Proud to join a bipartisan group today to introduce a bill to facilitate the creation of a national Native American veterans' monument
Today is the 50th Anniversary of the Equal Pay Act -- but women in every state still make less than their male counterparts. #EqualPayNow
On the 69th Anniversary of D-Day today, we honor the heroes who landed on the beaches of Normandy and achieved victory against all odds.
On Memorial Day, we come together to remember. Thank you to the brave men and women in uniform who have served our country.
I'm encouraged that the #Gangof8 comprehensive immigration reform bill passed out of committee. Still much work to be done on this issue.
As we recognize Peace Officers Memorial Day, please join me in paying tribute to the officers who have lost their lives in the line of duty.
Earlier I voted against the #PayChinaFirst bill. I will not prioritize China before American troops, veterans, seniors, and small biz owners
Today I voted to defend working families by voting no on H.R. 1406, which attempts to strip workers of the right to hard-earned overtime pay
Today is National Teacher Appreciation Day! Thanks to all of the teachers who are making a difference every day in the lives of our students
Tomorrow I'll be hosting an open house at my Hemet office located in Hemet City Hall. Hope to see you there!
As we celebrate #EarthDay, let us renew our commitment to protecting the environment and preserving our planet for generations to come
Excellent work by law enforcement & first responders in Boston over the past week. Prayers continue to be w/ the victims & people of Boston
I'm encouraged by the bipartisan immigration bill released in the Senate this week. Now is the time to act on #CIR
Deeply saddened by the explosions in Boston. My thoughts and prayers are with the people of Boston and the victims of this terrible tragedy
Very excited that I introduced my first bill today! My bill is focused on creating jobs and encouraging companies to do business in the U.S.
Had a great time at the Ramona Pageant Parade in San Jacinto this morning. Thanks to all who helped put this event together!
Yesterday I volunteered at the RAM free health clinic at the Indio fairgrounds. This clinic is open today and tomorrow. Spread the word!
I support marriage #equality and I'm proud to be speaking tonight at the Rally for Equality in Palm Springs. Hope to see you there!
Good news in Feb. #jobs report. Let's keep it up by passing a budget that promotes economic growth & puts us on a fiscally sustainable path
Proud to be one of the 212 Members of Congress who filed an amicus brief today in #SCOTUS opposing the discriminatory #DOMA
Today I voted to block a Congressional pay raise. Fiscal responsibility begins with ending wasteful taxpayer-funded pay raises for ourselves
This afternoon I met with Interior Secretary @KenSalazar and @SenatorBoxer to discuss our continued commitment to restoring the Salton Sea
Today is the 4th anniversary of the #LillyLedbetter #FairPay Act. We must continue to fight for equal pay for equal work for all Americans.
